author: cmpilato
msg: Pass an empty body rather than a NULL one to code that generates
body-less Neon requests so that Neon feels compelled to generate at
least a Content-Length header (which is of interest to some HTTP
proxies).  This effectively adds such a header to some DELETE,
MKACTIVITY, MKCOL, UNLOCK, and COPY requests.
* subversion/libsvn_ra_dav/ra_dav.h
(svn_ra_dav__request_dispatch): Add note about the benefits of using
the empty string ("") instead of NULL for body-less requests.
* subversion/libsvn_ra_dav/util.c
(svn_ra_dav__simple_request): Pass a NULL 'body' through was "" so
Neon still generates a Content-Length header.
